Songcasting lets the bard store a spell, which has a chance of being cast automatically each round that the bard sings their bard song. Immediately after casting this spell, the bard should attempt to cast another spell of 1st-level. Instead of being cast, this spell will be stored (expending one use of the spell).

Each round for the duration, if the bard is singing a bard song, there is a chance (1% per bard level) that the spell will be cast on each creature the bard song affects. Even spells with a range of Caster can target other creatures this way. The spell can potentially be triggered multiple times over many rounds.~
@37655     = ~Void Sound~
